Rendering things like text in the *world-view* can be done by moving the position of `Label`s that are **not** added to any stage, simply call the `draw` method directly on the `Label` and pass a `SpriteBatch` that has a projection matrix set from the world camera.

You can also forgo using `Label`s all together and &quot;*manually*&quot; render the text using direct draw-calls, this gives you a greater level of control at the cost of having to write a bit more code (I would do it this way).
The `BitmapFont`s `draw` method will be the basic way of doing this.[![enter image description here][1]][1]

In the example below I am using both techniques to display some text that appears next to a **Box2D** body and it is also affected by the zooming in that the camera does:

